<br>
I m only a lowly 46 Bard but love adding big mobs to my kill belt. I should also be able to summon a 54 Warrior, 55 Cleric, 53 Wizzie and 53 Enchanter if they are on. All are members of The Code.<br>
<br>
<br>
And it would be our privellage to assist you.<br>
<br>
I would like to join either the Nuke team (I pump mana good) or one of the general purpose teams for clearing random mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Here's a clip about your epic:<br>
<br>
Go to Kithicor, which is one zone off of Highpass. Find the Dark Elf House at +800, +2400. Give the box to any of the night spawns, causing General V'Ghera to spawn. Take him to a safe spot in the zone, preferably a zone and kill him. He is a very hard level 60 being. He is equal or better than any god. He quad attacks for 275 quite quickly, has a 1500pt harm touch and casts soul devour. He can also summon mobs from the zone to assist him. He is weak to Wizard Lure Line, Poison Spells, Scent Line, and Fire Based Spells. He is extremely strong against magic based spells so do not use it, it will just waste mana. The following strategy was found at the Safehouse. Here are what is recommended as groups:<br>
<br>
Gather together at min 36 players (6 full groups - more if they are split up) or up to about 50 if needed (it is reccomended that you do NOT get more then 50 or the zone may crash or too many will go LD and you will loose because of this) <br>
<br>
PULL TEAM: Quest Rogue with the &quot;sealed box&quot;, 56+ Shadow Knight OR Monk, and at least 2-3 56+ TANKS, and a 55+ Magi with CoH to summon the rogue after the hand off (total = 4-6 people) <br>
<br>
TANK TEAM: 56+ Cleric, 56+ Enchanter, 56+ Shaman, and 3 high level TANKS <br>
<br>
UNDEAD CONTROL DETAIL TEAM: All enchanters (as high lvl as possible) <br>
<br>
NUKE TEAM (there may be more then 1 nuke team): As many LURE available Wizards as possible!, Magi and Necros w/pets <br>
<br>
OTHERS: the best teams are composed of 4 tanks and 2 clerics to keep them alive, all the casters should be grouped into their own groups - no nukers with the tanks.<br>
<br>
Get the highest level players as possible - if you haven't got at least 2 teams of 56+ chars it is NOT recommended you do this battle.<br>
<br>
And here is how you kill him:<br>
<br>
1) Set up forces at the crossroads - +800, +3200. <br>
<br>
2) 3pm game time: Everyone Buffs Fully - Get all pets buffed. <br>
<br>
3) 4pm: Pull Team and Tank Team move to the ridge west of the DE cabin at location +800, +2400. <br>
<br>
4) Kill ALL Placeholderss in the cabin by 7pm (Except the Chaplain - if he aggros mesmerize and memory blur him) (note: this is done by only the pull and tank teams). <br>
<br>
5) Kill ALL nearby undead by 8pm, Everything. <br>
<br>
6) All pull team members get an invis to undead from the cleric (except for rogue) - may want to have spare invis to undead potions. <br>
<br>
7) Tank Team moves back to crossroads. <br>
<br>
8 .) 9pm: Chaplain will despawn - Begin speed buffing and DS buffs. <br>
<br>
9) Feign Death Puller (whether it be the Shadowknight or Monk) moves into cabin (near where the chaplain despawns but not on his spawn point) and Feign Deathss - NO NPCs should be in the cabin at this time, if one spawns other then the Coercer, KILL IT. <br>
<br>
10) Rogue moves to opposite side of cabin where the Feign Death puller will pull the coming Coercer to (this location needs to be far enough away from the cabin so that anyone walking into the cabin will not agro her but far enough away from all undead).<br>
<br>
11) 11pm: The Coercer spawns, FD puller pulls to the waiting Rogue (who is hidden and sneaking).<br>
<br>
12) Rogue gives box to the Coercer from behind while sneaking then rehides, General V'Ghera spawns a few seconds later (hand off needs to be fast so the Coercer does not return to the cabin) If the Rogue agros her just sit and die, DO NOT PULL TO GROUP, the cleric will get you later (make sure you get LOC) If the hand off is successful then have the Magi - who is still located at the base camp - Call of the Hero the Rogue back to camp and get ready for the incoming General. <br>
<br>
13) Highest level tank on the pull team pulls the General to the waiting forces at the crossroads - make sure you do not get too far away from the General or he will go back to the cabin (if the first tank dies while pulling then the second highest tank on the pull team will take over and so on until the General is at the camp) NOTE: Call of Hero can be used to bring the Feign Death puller and Rogue back to camp safely - use this only when you have a magician in pull team that stays in camp during pull.<br>
<br>
14) All forces at crossroads engage - EXCEPT the Enchanters... ALL (or at min 2) the Enchanters will have the sole responsibility of keeping the undead that arrive mesmerized (Mainly the healers) Since the General is level 63 his corpse will not rot for 30 minutes - the Rogue should loot first, make sure to get the &quot;General's Pouch&quot; and IF it drops the &quot;Cazic Quill.&quot; You will be very lucky if it drops the Cazic Quill. If he doesn't then you must do the sub-quest. All other loot from the General is NOT needed for the quest and SHOULD be given out to the helping forces - distribute however you see fit.<br>
<br>
Go back to Stanos in Highpass Hold and turn in the Jagged Diamond Dagger, Cazic's Quill, and the General's Pouch for the Ragebringer<br>
<br>
<br>
